@startuml
title Dow Jones Hammer - Security Audit Control Flow

actor User
participant "Slack Bot" as Slack
participant "REST API" as API
participant "API Gateway" as APIGW
participant "Initiation Lambda" as InitLambda
participant "SNS Topic" as SNS
participant "Identification Lambda" as IdLambda
participant "AWS Services\n(S3, IAM, EBS, RDS, SQS, EC2)" as AWSServices
participant "DynamoDB\n(Issues Table)" as DDB
participant "Reporting EC2" as ReportingEC2
participant "JIRA" as JIRA
participant "Slack Notifications" as SlackNotif
participant "Remediation Lambda" as RemLambda
participant "S3 Bucket\n(Reports & Backups)" as S3
participant "CloudWatch Logs" as CWLogs

== Automated Scheduled Scan ==
activate InitLambda
InitLambda -> InitLambda: Load config.json\n(accounts, regions, checks)
InitLambda -> SNS: Publish identification events\nfor each security check
activate SNS
SNS -> IdLambda: Trigger Identification Lambda
deactivate SNS
deactivate InitLambda

== Identification Phase ==
activate IdLambda
IdLambda -> IdLambda: Load configuration\n(security check parameters)
IdLambda -> AWSServices: Query resources\n(multi-account, multi-region)
activate AWSServices
AWSServices --> IdLambda: Return resource configurations
deactivate AWSServices

IdLambda -> IdLambda: Apply security rules\n(Check violations)
IdLambda -> IdLambda: Check whitelist.json\n(filter exceptions)

IdLambda -> DDB: Store identified issues
activate DDB
DDB --> IdLambda: Confirm storage
deactivate DDB

IdLambda -> CWLogs: Log identification results
activate CWLogs
deactivate CWLogs
deactivate IdLambda

== Reporting Phase ==
activate ReportingEC2
ReportingEC2 -> DDB: Query identified issues
activate DDB
DDB --> ReportingEC2: Return issues list
deactivate DDB

ReportingEC2 -> ReportingEC2: Load ticket_owners.json\n(map issues to teams)
ReportingEC2 -> ReportingEC2: Generate CSV reports

ReportingEC2 -> S3: Upload CSV reports
activate S3
S3 --> ReportingEC2: Confirm upload
deactivate S3

ReportingEC2 -> JIRA: Create/Update tickets
activate JIRA
JIRA --> ReportingEC2: Return ticket IDs
ReportingEC2 -> JIRA: Add comments/attachments
JIRA --> ReportingEC2: Confirm updates
deactivate JIRA

ReportingEC2 -> SlackNotif: Send notifications\n(issue alerts)
activate SlackNotif
SlackNotif --> ReportingEC2: Confirm delivery
deactivate SlackNotif

ReportingEC2 -> CWLogs: Log reporting actions
activate CWLogs
deactivate CWLogs
deactivate ReportingEC2

== Manual Scan via REST API ==
User -> API: Request on-demand scan\n(specific check/account)
activate API
API -> APIGW: Forward request
activate APIGW
APIGW -> InitLambda: Trigger initiation
activate InitLambda
InitLambda -> SNS: Publish events
activate SNS
SNS -> IdLambda: Trigger Lambda
deactivate SNS
deactivate InitLambda
activate IdLambda
note right: Identification flow\n(same as scheduled)
IdLambda -> DDB: Store results
IdLambda --> APIGW: Return scan results
deactivate IdLambda
APIGW --> API: Return response
deactivate APIGW
API --> User: Show results
deactivate API

== Slack Bot Interaction ==
User -> Slack: Send command\n(query status/trigger scan)
activate Slack
Slack -> API: Call API endpoint
activate API
API -> DDB: Query issue status
activate DDB
DDB --> API: Return issue data
deactivate DDB
API --> Slack: Format response
deactivate API
Slack --> User: Display results
deactivate Slack

== Automated Remediation Phase ==
activate RemLambda
RemLambda -> DDB: Query issues\nmarked for auto-remediation
activate DDB
DDB --> RemLambda: Return issues list
deactivate DDB

RemLambda -> RemLambda: Load config.json\n(remediation settings)
RemLambda -> RemLambda: Check whitelist.json\n(verify not whitelisted)

RemLambda -> AWSServices: Backup current config
activate AWSServices
AWSServices --> RemLambda: Config backup
RemLambda -> S3: Store backup
activate S3
S3 --> RemLambda: Confirm storage
deactivate S3

RemLambda -> AWSServices: Execute remediation\n(e.g., disable keys,\nrestrict access)
AWSServices --> RemLambda: Confirm action
deactivate AWSServices

RemLambda -> DDB: Update issue status\n(mark as remediated)
activate DDB
DDB --> RemLambda: Confirm update
deactivate DDB

RemLambda -> JIRA: Update ticket\n(add remediation comment)
activate JIRA
JIRA --> RemLambda: Confirm update
RemLambda -> JIRA: Close ticket if resolved
JIRA --> RemLambda: Ticket closed
deactivate JIRA

RemLambda -> SlackNotif: Send remediation notification
activate SlackNotif
SlackNotif --> RemLambda: Confirm delivery
deactivate SlackNotif

RemLambda -> CWLogs: Log remediation actions
activate CWLogs
deactivate CWLogs
deactivate RemLambda

== Manual Remediation ==
User -> JIRA: Review ticket details
activate JIRA
JIRA --> User: Show issue information
deactivate JIRA
User -> AWSServices: Manually fix issue
activate AWSServices
AWSServices --> User: Confirm fix
deactivate AWSServices
User -> JIRA: Close ticket
activate JIRA
JIRA -> DDB: Update issue status
activate DDB
DDB --> JIRA: Confirm update
deactivate DDB
deactivate JIRA

@enduml
